Singapore Senior Minister Admitted to Hospital
SINGAPORE , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- Singapore Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew was admitted to the National University Hospital Saturday for treatment of an infection arising from a minor surgical procedure , Television Corporation of Singapore ( TCS ) reported Sunday .
The TCS quoted his office as saying that his condition is stable and he is currently on intravenous antibiotics .
The TCS said the senior minister is expected to remain in hospital for the next few days .
